Daniel arap Moi, Reuter reports from Nairobi. Western donors suspended aid
worth about Dollars 40m a month 16 months ago to pressure Mr Moi into
embracing radical political and economic reforms. An IMF team is due in
Kenya on February 21 to make a report.
