FT  09 FEB 93 / Algiers extends emergency
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By FRANCIS GHILES
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
Algerian leaders have extended indefinitely the state of emergency, imposed
a year ago after suspended elections which the Islamic Salvation Front was
poised to win, writes Francis Ghiles.
The country's five-man presidency, meeting under head of state Mr Ali Kafi,
said at the weekend that it had extended the emergency, in what was
interpreted as a demonstration of its determination to crush Islamic
fundamentalism.
