FT  09 FEB 93 / International Company News: Hispano Suiza attracts second
bid
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By PETER BRUCE
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
   MADRID
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
THE remnants of one of the shooting stars of the Madrid bourse in the 1980s
are to be fought over at an extraordinary shareholders meeting of the
Hispano Suiza group in Madrid on Thursday with the sudden emergence of two
bids for its remaining assets.
It emerged yesterday that Azkoyen, a Pamplona-based producer of vending
machines, has bid for the 92 per cent of Hispano Suiza owned by a consortium
of blue chip UK financial companies.
The bid values Hispano Suiza at just Pta492m (Dollars 4.24m), a far cry from
the Pta3bn it was once worth on the market.
That bid may block one made a few weeks ago by a consortium led by Mr Juan
Abello, a Spanish financier, with support from the Bonomi family of Italy,
which controls the Saffa paper group.
The Abello bid was worth Pta1.011bn but only included Hispano Suiza's
profitable building materials companies.
Thursday's meeting was called to approve the Abello bid but shareholders may
now reconsider.
