FT  09 FEB 93 / UK Company News: Butte Mining losses double to Pounds 13.5m
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By KENNETH GOODING
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
BUTTE MINING, which is claiming damages of at least Dollars 325m (Pounds
214m) in the US against more than 70 former directors, advisers and
investors, saw losses before tax for the year to June 30 nearly double from
Pounds 7m to Pounds 13.5m, writes Kenneth Gooding.
The latest figures included an exceptional Pounds 8.7m loss from writing
down all assets to 'values that should be realisable in today's economic
climate,' said Mr David Lloyd-Jacob, chairman.
He said that the new management team had investigated circumstances
surrounding two acquisitions in Montana and the purchase of Gramcol-Zircon
in the UK. 'Serious deficiencies were discovered,' he said. Litigation and
warranty claims have been started and information passed to the Serious
Fraud Office, 'which is investigating all three transactions.'
