</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
THE pension age for women should be raised to 65 and the common retirement
age raised eventually to 67, the Social Market Foundation, an independent
think tank, argues in a report published today
It was written by Mr David Willetts, Conservative MP for Havant and a member
