<HEADLINE>
FT  08 FEB 93 / Observer: Overkill
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
Whatever problems the BBC will face in its intense battle with commercial
rivals in future, lack of strategic advice is not going to be one of them.
Although thousands of jobs are likely to be axed, new BBC boss John Birt has
earmarked one area for expansion - the policy &amp; planning directorate, headed
by newly promoted Patricia Hodgson.
The Beeb is advertising for: a chief adviser, commercial and business
policy; a head of strategy evaluation; and a head of business information
both reporting to a new chief adviser, corporate strategy. Such appointments
make it increasingly hard to take seriously John Birt's vaunted war on BBC
bureaucracy.
</TEXT>
