shareholders that there was a deficit of shareholders' funds on March 31
1992 of Pounds 31.9m. 'Subsequently UK Land has been engaged in extensive
negotiations with its bankers with a view to implementing a capital
reorganisation. An announcement will be made upon the conclusion of these
negotiations,' it said.
It made a loss of Pounds 17.1m for the 18-months to March 31 after an
exceptional Pounds 20m for estimated liabilities incurred in development
programmes.
